HEALTHNET NEWS FOR DEVELOPING COUNTRIES
************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
<http://www.fas.org/ahead>

**********************************
Please note that there are certain eligibility criteria to receive HealthNet
News. Clinicians and other interested health professionals ONLY in the
DEVELOPING WORLD may subscribe.
[This is because the copyright waivers generously given by the medical
journals only extend to developing countries - Mod.JW]
**********************************
Dear SatelLife Discussion Group Participant:
The following Table of Contents page is from a recent issue of HealthNet
News. For those of you who do not already know, HealthNet News is a
newsletter that is compiled at SatelLife and is sent out weekly to health
professionals in the developing world. The newsletter contains current
research and medical information (abstracts, summaries, editorials, full
text articles, etc.) from peer-reviewed journals. The newsletter provides
relevant, practical, and useful information to those in developing nations
who would not otherwise not have this available to them. HealthNet News
enables health professionals to keep abreast of topical matters in health
and
medicine and use them in their own work.
We are sending you this Table of Contents from HealthNet News and invite
you to subscribe. Please share our newsletter with your colleagues and
friends and encourage others who would benefit from this free electronic
weekly publication to subscribe as well.
To subscribe to HealthNet News:
Send an email message to majordomo@usa.healthnet.org
Type the following command in the body of your message: subscribe hnn
Please note that there are certain eligibility criteria to receive HealthNet
News. Clinicians and other interested health professionals ONLY in the
DEVELOPING WORLD may subscribe, by following the above directions.
